---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const siteName = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_SITE_NAME ?? "PricingNest";
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost) | ${siteName}`}
  description="CAC definition, what to include, and how CAC connects to payback period and break-even pricing."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <h1>CAC (Customer Acquisition Cost)</h1>
    <p>CAC is how much you spend to acquire a customer. It’s most useful when paired with gross profit and payback period.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="grid">
    <article class="card col8">
      <h2>What to include</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Paid acquisition spend (ads, affiliates), plus agency/creative if material.</li>
        <li>Sales compensation and tooling if you have a sales-assisted motion.</li>
        <li>Onboarding or implementation costs if they scale with new customers.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">How to use CAC</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li>Pair CAC with gross profit per month to estimate payback.</li>
        <li>Use a “break-even CAC” target when you set a price floor.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top: 1.25rem;">Tools to use</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/cac-payback-period-calculator/">CAC payback period calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/break-even-cac-calculator/">Break-even CAC calculator</a></li>
        <li><a href="/saas-pricing/ltv-calculator/">LTV calculator</a></li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <aside class="card col4">
      <h2>Related</h2>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><a href="/glossary/cac-payback/">CAC payback</a></li>
        <li><a href="/glossary/ltv/">LTV</a></li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

